She looked up at Destructor. "Why are you helping me if you think 
that I know nothing?"  Then she figured that he was reeling her in 
for a kill.  then she cught a whiff of a scent.  if was strangely 
familiar.  She stopped in her tracks as she remembered where she knew 
that scent. BLACK ARACNIA.  She looked at Destructor.  SO that is 
where he was taiking her, he was taking her to see Aracnia, she 
thought.  She just looked at Destructor.  There was no chance for 
escape, no chance for getting away.  She couldn't out run the 
autuguns of the ship.  She was trapped, trapped like a mouse.  She 
looked down as the floor and gave a deep sigh.  She couldn't figure 
out what she ever did so wrong that she deserved this fate.
